<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1194,1398]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Description.— 
<taxonomicName box="[364,484,1230,1254]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Barbaloba" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[364,484,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Barbaloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
possesses a unique combination of male features that include: absence of a proximal flange and middle region of dorsal part of valva developed into a large, ventrally projecting, setose lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,1194,1398]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Etymology. The generic name 
<taxonomicName box="[550,670,1302,1326]" class="Insecta" family="Blastobasidae" genus="Barbaloba" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[550,670,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Barbaloba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from two Latin words, 
<emphasis box="[1065,1132,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">barba</emphasis>
a femanine noun meaning beard, and 
<emphasis box="[285,345,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">lobus</emphasis>
, a masculine noun meaning a rounded projection, and refers to the setose lobelike process originating from the ventral part of the valva of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
